The paper deals with lower bounds and identity testing for arithmetic circuits, which are central topics in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The focus is on depth-3 circuits, which are a specific type of arithmetic circuits, and read-once algebraic branching programs (ROABP), which are a related model of computation. Therefore, categories related to circuit complexity, such as cs.CC, cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), and cs.SC (symbolic computation), are likely. The paper also introduces a new notion of distance for multilinear depth-3 circuits, which is a combinatorial concept, suggesting categories such as cs.CG (computational geometry) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
